The Second Commandment of Love

Filial Movement Toward God

The charity that is poured into our hearts by the Holy Spirit makes us children of God and relates us to the Word in the bosom of the Holy Trinity. It finds, in this filial character, its essential movement.

--

NP NRSVCE
The spirit that is given us cries: Abba, Father! It makes us co-heirs with Christ. > Romans 8:15-17 - NRSVCE
> 15b. When we cry, “Abba! Father!”
> 16. it is that very Spirit bearing witness with our spirit that we are children of God,
> 17. and if children, then heirs, heirs of God and joint heirs with Christ — if, in fact, we suffer with him so that we may also be glorified with him.
Through it, the soul sighs after its share in the heritage that is God Himself. > Romans 8:22-23 - NRSVCE
> 22. We know that the whole creation has been groaning in labor pains until now;
> 23. and not only the creation, but we ourselves, who have the first fruits of the Spirit, groan inwardly while we wait for adoption, the redemption of our bodies.
While waiting until hope is fulfilled in the bosom of the Father, the Holy Spirit sustains and guides the longing of the soul in the dark night of here below. > Romans 8:26-27 - NRSVCE
> 26. Likewise the Spirit helps us in our weakness; for we do not know how to pray as we ought, but that very Spirit intercedes with sighs too deep for words.
> 27. And God, who searches the heart, knows what is the mind of the Spirit, because the Spirit intercedes for the saints according to the will of God.

note -- glory != heaven; rather, God's glory fills the earth and Jesus (and we) are revealed as sons; creation is to be renewed under our stewardship

note -- v.26-27 vocation to suffering; v.27 trinitarian
